Author:
Vol / Page:  I 53/681
Edition:
Quote:  Sale of Liquor Act... 61. Liquor permit for unlicensed restaurant... The Chairman of the Licensing Committee.. may at any time grant to any person conducting the business of a restaurateur in any

unlicensed restaurant.. a permit authorising the consumption of liquor in the restaurant by any person who is there for the purpose of partaking of a meal and who brings the liquor with him into the restaurant.
